# basic commands
# ls        shows whats in current working directory
# ls -l     shows file permissions
# cd        change directory
# cd ..     change directory one back
# cd /      change to OG folder
# nano      opens in text editor
# sudo touch <yourstupidfile.doc> </a/location/here/>            creates file
# mv <yourstupidfile.doc> </a/location/here>            moves a file
# cp <copiablefile.doc> </a/location/here/>  OR  </a/file/here/>         copies a file
# rm <aremovablefile.doc>           deletes a file
# chmod a+rwx /path/to/file          Gives full permission to a singular file
# sudo chmod -R a+rwx /path/to/folder          Gives full permission for folder and files inside

# Locations of important things for the webserver
# /var/www/      contains wordpress and php
# /etc/netplan/   Contains static configuration for networks
# /etc/phpmyadmin/    configuration apache and php
